The paper discusses a communication system for IoT devices that relies on RF energy harvesting and backscatter communication. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a sparse-coded modulation algorithm, which involves coding theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed system also involves multiple access techniques, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses simulation results, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) for visualizing and analyzing the data.
